Method Description <code>await run(fake=False)</code> Apply all pending migrations. <code>fake=True</code> records them without executing SQL. <code>await plan()</code> Return the SQL that <code>run()</code> would execute, without touching the database. <code>await ensure_tracking_table()</code> Create <code>_bitemporalorm_migrations</code> if it does not exist. Called automatically by <code>run()</code>. <p>The tracking table <code>_bitemporalorm_migrations</code> records the name of each applied migration:</p> <pre><code>CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS _bitemporalorm_migrations (
    name       TEXT NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY,
    applied_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
);
</code></pre>
